    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nwildmenu arrow navigation makes no sense when `pum` is enabled.\r\nLeft/Right arrow keys map to Up/Down navigation in the menu - leading to people inventing [hacky ways](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/76352066/nvim-autocomplete-menu-arrow-selection-invert-left-right-up-down-functions) of fixing the default behavior.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nAdd a `wildoptions=swapnav` that makes Up/Down cycle through match list and Left/Right navigate directories, swapping the default (Left/Right cycle, Up/Down dirs).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40063#discussion_r3330097896"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/40063"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3330097896"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "naming nit: \"swap\" is understood to refer to \"swapfiles\", so if we can avoid it, that helps user intuition (UX).\n\nalso 'swapnav' is not an option thus should not use single-quotes. hence the failing CI lint job.\n\nsuggestion:   `pumnav` makes the relationship to `pum` explicit, so users who already set `wildoptions=pum` will recognize the parallel.\n\n\n```suggestion\n• 'wildoptions' \"pumnav\" flag swaps wildmenu arrow key roles: Up/Down\n```",
            "commit_id": "26e083823e86c7326047b1e81c599fb0e514cf97",
            "created_at": "2026-05-31T11:04:20Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -217,6 +217,8 @@ OPTIONS\n • 'shortmess' flag |shm-u| silences undo/redo messages.\n • 'statusline' supports |stl-%0{| to insert the expression result verbatim.\n • 'winpinned' prevents window from closing unless specifically targeted.\n+• 'wildoptions' 'swapnav' flag swaps wildmenu arrow key roles: Up/Down",
